  <p>The main operation for all SSSP algorithms discussed in this visualiza=
tion is the <samp>relax(u, v, w(u, v))</samp> operation with the following =
pseudo-code:</p><pre>relax(u, v, w_u_v)<br>  if D[v] &gt; D[u]+w_u_v // if =
the path can be shortened<br>    D[v] =3D D[u]+w_u_v // we 'relax' this edg=
e<br>    p[v] =3D u // remember/update the predecessor<br>    // update som=
e other data structure(s) as necessary</pre><p>For example, see <samp>relax=
(1,2,4)</samp> operation on the figure below: <img src=3D"https://visualgo.=
net/img/relax.png" width=3D"500" alt=3D"relax operation example"></p>

