eft:50%;margin-left:-250px;width:500px;">
  <p>The general purpose <b>Bellman-Ford algorithm</b> can solve <b>all kin=
ds</b> of valid SSSP problem variants (expect one =E2=80=94 the one that is=
 ill-defined anyway, to be discussed soon), albeit with a <b>rather slow</b=
> O(<b>V=C3=97E</b>) running time. It also has an extremely simple pseudo-c=
ode:</p><pre>for i =3D 1 to |V|-1 // O(V) here, so O(V=C3=97E=C3=971) =3D O=
(V=C3=97E)<br>  for each edge(u, v) =E2=88=88 E // O(E) here, e.g. by using=
 an Edge List<br>    relax(u, v, w(u, v)) // O(1) here</pre><p>Without furt=
her ado, let's see a preview of how it works on the example graph above by =
clicking <span class=3D"slide-actions">BellmanFord(0)</span> (=E2=89=8830s,=
 and for now, please ignore the additional loop at the bottom of the pseudo=
-code).</p>

