the same time complexity analysis of O((<b>V</b>+<b>E</b>) log <b>V</b>).</=
p><br><p>PS: We note that when we use the Modified Dijkstra's algorithm, th=
ere can be more items (up to <b>E</b>) in the Priority Queue than if we use=
 the Original Dijkstra's algorithm (up to <b>V</b>). However, since O(log <=
b>E</b>) =3D O(log <b>V^2</b>) =3D O(2 log <b>V</b>) =3D O(log <b>V</b>), w=
e still treat the Priority Queue operations as O(log <b>V</b>).</p><br><p>H=
owever, if the graph has at least one negative weight edge, the analysis is=
 harder.</p>

